The issue here is that you're trying to use a Hook (`useFilters`) inside a class component (`DirectoryListing`). Hooks can only be used inside function components or other Hooks.

To solve this issue, you have two options:

1. **Convert your class component to a function component.** Here's how you could do this:

```jsx
import React, { useState, useEffect } from 'react';
import AudioPlayerSmall from '../audioplayer/audio-player-small';
import { useFilters } from '../FilterContext';
import chroma from 'chroma-js';

function DirectoryListing(props) {
  const { selectedFilters } = useFilters();

  const getListingList = () => {
    const listingList = [];
    props.listingQuery.forEach(listing => {
      listingList.push({
        title: listing.title,
        website: listing.website,
        episodeURL: listing.episodeURL,
        episodePromo: listing.episodePromo,
        color: listing.color,
      });
    });
    return listingList;
  };

  const listingList = getListingList();

  return (
    <div className="directory-list">
      {listingList.map(listing => {
        const isSelected = selectedFilters.includes(listing.metadata);
        const backgroundColor = isSelected ? chroma.scale(['white', 'red'])(0.5) : 'white';

        return (
          <React.Fragment key={listing.title}>
            <div className={`directory-block--item ${backgroundColor}`}>
              {/* ... */}
            </div>
          </React.Fragment>
        );
      })}
    </div>
  );
}

export default DirectoryListing;
```

2. **Move the logic that uses the Hook to a separate function component, and use this component inside `DirectoryListing`.** This way, you can keep `DirectoryListing` as a class component. Here's how you could do this:

```jsx
import React from 'react';
import AudioPlayerSmall from '../audioplayer/audio-player-small';
import { useFilters } from '../FilterContext';
import chroma from 'chroma-js';

function Listing({ listing }) {
  const { selectedFilters } = useFilters();
  const isSelected = selectedFilters.includes(listing.metadata);
  const backgroundColor = isSelected ? chroma.scale(['white', 'red'])(0.5) : 'white';

  return (
    <React.Fragment key={listing.title}>
      <div className={`directory-block--item ${backgroundColor}`}>
        {/* ... */}
      </div>
    </React.Fragment>
  );
}

class DirectoryListing extends React.Component<any, any> {
  getListingList() {
    // ...
  }

  render() {
    const listingList = this.getListingList();

    return (
      <div className="directory-list">
        {listingList.map(listing => (
          <Listing listing={listing} />
        ))}
      </div>
    );
  }
}

export default DirectoryListing;
```

In this example, `Listing` is a new function component that uses the `useFilters` Hook and renders a single listing. This component is used inside the `DirectoryListing` class component.

